# ===================================
# HOW TO GENERATE SECURE SECRETS
# ===================================
# Run this command in terminal to generate a 256-bit secret:
#
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
#
# This will output something like:
#   a1b2c3d4e5f6789abc123def456789012345678901234567890abcdef123456
#
# Copy this value and use it for JWT_SECRET and REFRESH_SECRET
# Generate DIFFERENT secrets for each!

# ===================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ===================================
# 1. NEVER commit .env to git
# 2. Rotate secrets regularly (monthly recommended)
# 3. Use different secrets for development and production
# 4. Store production secrets in secure vault (AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)
# 5. Enable 2FA for all service accounts (Email, Payment gateways, etc.)
